flavor_text_entries.emerald:
It lives in water virtually all day long.
Its body color and pattern act as
camouflage that makes it tough for
enemies to spot in water.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
By keeping still
and listening in­
tently, it can tell what is in
even wild, fast-
moving rivers.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
When it plays in
water, it rolls up
its elongated ears to prevent their
insides from get­
ting wet.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
The bubble-like
pattern on its
stomach helps it camouflage itself
when it's in the
water.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
AZUMARILL’s long ears are indispensable
sensors. By focusing its hearing, this
POKéMON can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and
fast-running rivers.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
AZUMARILL can make balloons out of
air. It makes these air balloons if it
spots a drowning POKéMON. The air balloons enable the POKéMON in
trouble to breathe.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
When it plays in water, it rolls up its
elongated ears to prevent their insides
from getting wet.
flavor_text_entries.leafgreen:
By keeping still and listening intently, it
can even tell what is in wild, fast-moving

flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It lives in rivers and lakes. In
water, its coloring and patterns
trick the vision of foes.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
Its long ears are superb sensors.
It can distinguish the movements
of living things on riverbeds.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
It can spend all day in water,
since it can inhale and store
a large volume of air.

Azumarill’s long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its
hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are

flavor_text_entries.alpha-sapphire:
Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air
balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons
enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.
flavor_text_entries.sword:
It spends most of its time in the water. On sunny
days, Azumarill floats on the surface of the water
and sunbathes.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When
Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them
with these bubbles.
